description:
Spec bl-2e26 §13 ('prime != install, but prime --install fuses them on demand'). REDO of the first cut (commit 88e585e, bl-6e93), which VIOLATED the §0 structural invariant "the tracker plugin is the only thing that talks to a remote": that cut had CORE run `git fetch <center>` directly in src/adopt.rs (and had to weaken the git::run doc comment to excuse it). REVERT it.

CORRECT DESIGN: core handles transfers between LOCAL checkouts ONLY; the tracker — the sole remote-talker — performs the actual remote fetch, wired as an install HOOK. Sequence for `bl prime --install <center>`:
(1) ensure local substrate (existing prime path);
(2) run an install chain whose `install.pre` tracker hook FETCHES the center's balls/config branch into a local ref, leaving it at FETCH_HEAD (a git-standard ref — no invented core<->plugin convention/coupling);
(3) CORE materializes that LOCAL ref (worktree --detach FETCH_HEAD) and path-copies config/ -> landing (install lib, folder=mirror), then SEALS (commit) onto the landing;
(4) a final prime+sync brings the just-adopted tasks_branch to readiness.

WHY this works now without solving the whole install run-wiring: the ADOPT direction's seal target is ALWAYS the local landing — unambiguous — so this needs only minimal install-as-hooked-op wiring, NOT the publish-direction seal-target resolution (that stays bl-66e7). Publish (`install --to <center>`, tracker push as install.post) is OUT OF SCOPE here.

INVARIANT RESTORED: no `git fetch` / remote call anywhere in core; strip the tracker and prime --install simply cannot reach a remote (it degrades, never violates). SINGLE hop, not a walk: a center's config names its own tasks_branch (§4), never another config to chase. Each install idempotent -> a failed adopt RESUMES. Plain prime stays auto-safe (the --install flag IS the consent).

TOUCHES: core (revert the core fetch in src/adopt.rs; run the install.pre chain + seal-to-landing), the tracker (add an install-op handler that fetches the --from config branch — it already does `git fetch remote balls/config` in store_elsewhere, so a few lines), seed config/plugins.toml (`install.pre = ["tracker"]`).

DEPS: bl-3dd9 (install path-copy lib — reused for the LOCAL copy), bl-cd21 (--remote>--center>XDG>origin resolution + the <center> remote). Supersedes the flawed core-fetch cut.
